To assess whether a pair of traits share pathways higher than chance expectation, we first determined the pathways that were significantly associated with each trait (pcombined < 0.01), followed by Fisher’s Exact Test. Specifically, for two traits a and b, we build a dichotomous 2 × 2 contingency table as follows:
